  "about": {
    "title": "About DFR Browser 2",
    "content": "DFR Browser 2 is an interactive web application for exploring topic models and document collections. It is based on the original <a href=\"https://agoldst.github.io/dfr-browser/\" target=\"_blank\">DFR Browser</a> created by Andrew Goldstone. However, it has been re-engineered from the ground up with new features. These include:\n\n**Features:**\n\n- Updated <a href=\"https://getbootstrap.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Bootstrap</a> and <a href=\"https://d3js.org/\" target=\"_blank\">D3</a> libraries\n- Page routing with <a href=\"https://visionmedia.github.io/page.js/\" target=\"_blank\">page.js</a>\n- Multilingual sorting capabilities\n- Embargo-controlled document access\n- Optional upload form for MALLET data and metadata\n- Handling of bibliography using CSL-JSON fields\n- Overall, a fresh look\n\nThe future repository for DFR Browser 2 will be <a href=\"https://github.com/scottkleinman/dfr-browser2\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/scottkleinman/dfr-browser2</a>.\n\nYou can customise the content of this page in the `config.json` file."
